Nor has it anything to do with the recent disclosure of more than four million diplomatic documents from the US, but with the allegations of sexual abuse that Australians face in Sweden.
Mark Stephens, Wikileaks' founder's lawyer, also assures that "the police know where and how to contact Mr Assange."
